text: California State University, Sacramento, also known as Sacramento State University, is a public university in Sacramento, California. The university has about 29,241 students. It was founded in 1947. The current president of the university is Alexander Gonzalez. ==Sports== The men's and women's sports teams of the university are called the Hornets. They have 21 varsity teams, almost all of which play in the Big Sky Conference. The baseball team plays in the Western Athletic Conference, and the women's rowing team is in the American Athletic Conference. ==Other websites== *California State University, Sacramento's Official website *Sacramento State Hornets' Official athletics website Category:Big Sky Conference Category:California State University Category:Sacramento, California Category:1947 establishments in the United States Category:1940s establishments in California
